AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION!!! Meet Beautiful Bella a Border Collie mix born around August 2016. Bella is a bit shy when you first meet her but warms up to show her affectionate and loving side. She was recently rescued from an area shelter. She is adjusting well in her foster home with her fosters dog and cat. Bella is a loyal girl that will make a wonderful companion. She loves attention and to be with her person. She is treat motivated and a quick learner. She is a cuddly girl that will crawl in your lap if you let her. She is house trained and does well in the crate. Bella is current on vaccines, microchipped and around 45lbs. Bella would not do well with an underground fence system but is good on leash or in a structural fenced in yard. She would be best suited in a home with children 10 years and older. Will make a wonderful addition to the right family and will the best buddy you will ever have. Just look at this adorable, loving boy! Lane and the rest of his family was abandoned by his humans and left to fend for themselves in the woods. When they were found, Lane was up on a berm, across a creek and he wanted to be saved so badly that he actually swam the creek to get to his rescuer. She had gone to feed them but could not leave without him. Lane had been in her home only 24 hours when she brought him to me for photos and he was so calm and comfortable and content to even want belly rubs. He loves to be held and has no interest in going back outside. Lane is the ideal easy-going cat who gets along well with other cats, dogs and rabbits. He is quiet, confident and comfortable by himself, but loves belly rubs and purring while curled up in a lap.  He adapts easily to new environments. Lane is pretty much purrfect and will be a fabulous feline for a loving home. He is about 6 months old, 5 lbs and will be fully vetted before adoption. Contact friendswoodanimaladvocates@gmail.com to meet him.
